content:
Add a Dashboard Component in Salesforce Classic

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)
Available in: Group (View Only), Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To create dashboards: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you created: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To add a component:
Click Edit on the dashboard where you want to add a component.
Drag the component type from the Components tab onto your dashboard.
You can also drop the data source first, then drop a component type onto it.

Component types:
Use a chart when you want to show data graphically.
Use a gauge when you have a single value that you want to show within a range of custom values
Use a metric when you have one key value to display.
Use a table to show a set of report data in column form.
Visualforce Page: use to create a custom component or show information not available in another component type.
Custom S-Control: can contain any type of content that you can display in a browser.

Drag a report from the Data Sources tab onto the component you just dropped on the dashboard.
On the Component Data tab, choose which summary fields and groupings in the underlying report you want to display in your component.
Make more fields available for a dashboard component by adding them to the source report chart.
On the Formatting tab, specify how your component shows its data.

To remove a component:
Click on your dashboard component.
Click to remove it from the component.
Click to remove it from the dashboard.
Click component header, title, and footer fields to edit them.
title: Adding Components to Salesforce Dashboards
